The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Dinda, Saha receive Grade D contracts
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Dinda, Saha receive Grade D contracts
            A STAFF REPORTER AMP; AGENCIES                                Calcutta/New Delhi: Bengal pacer Ashok Dinda and wicketkeeper Wriddhiman Saha found a place in Grade D as the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) offered new contracts to 37 players.         
	Dinda and Saha will get richer by Rs 15 lakh each. The BCCI named 14 players in Grade D. Dinda, who took five wickets for Bengal against Vidarbha on Monday in the Ranji Trophy Plate Group match, was rewarded for his consistent performance in the ongoing domestic season.         
	Saha scored a scintillating 159 for Bengal on Sunday to help the side take a first innings lead against Vidarbha.         
	Bengal batsman Manoj Tiwary didnt find a place in the contracts.         
	Meanwhile, his prolonged slump in form notwithstanding, Rahul Dravid retained his place in Grade A. The players have been clubbed in four grades in the new contract which would cover the October 2008  September 2009 period, BCCI secretary N. Srinivasan said in a statement.         
	The quartet of Virender Sehwag, Gautam Gambhir, Harbhajan Singh and V.V.S. Laxman were promoted to Grade A.         
	Wicketkeeper-batsman Dinesh Karthik was dropped to Grade D from his previous Grade B place.                                                                                                                          
